                "recommendations": [
                    {
                        "id": 6,
                        "protocol": 4,
                        "content": "<p>Try to determine the underlying reason that might be causing caregiver distress and being able to assess the severity of the distress. If the client is at undue risk, the need to call 911 may be required even if the client\u2019s GOC are to remain at home. <br><\/p><p><b>Emergency situations  <\/b><\/p><ul><li>Suicidal ideation and\/or plan in place \u2013 refer to Crisis Line 1-800-784-2433<\/li><li>Extreme caregiver agitation unable to assess over the phone resulting in high risk to client<\/li><li>Do you feel safe? Client becoming abusive and threatening to caregiver<\/li><\/ul><div><p><b>Consider<\/b><\/p><ul><li>Use a calming voice<\/li><li>Listen, don\u2019t interrupt or rush <\/li><li>Allow silence, be mindful and use empathic listening<\/li><li>\u201cWhat is concerning you most\u201d<\/li><li>\u201cHelp me understand a bit more\u201d<\/li><li>\u201cYou sound upset\u2026\u201d <\/li><li>\u201cWhat I\u2019m hearing is\u2026do you feel that\u2019s accurate?<\/li><li>\u201cWhat have you done in the past that has been helpful?\u201d<\/li><li>\u201cHow are you feeling now?\u201d<\/li><li>If the short term plan is to get through till the morning ask: \u201cIs there anyone you can call to come to the home?\u201d<\/li><\/ul><p><br><\/p><\/div>",
                        "title": "Non-Pharmaceutical Interventions"
                    }
